-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing_events.sql
-- Deduplicate billing_events to one record per subscription and event_month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_id,
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    event_id,
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/fact/fct_subscription_metrics.sql
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        DATE_TRUNC('month', be.event_month) AS month,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry,
        COUNT(DISTINCT s.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
        SUM(COALESCE(p.monthly_price, 0)) AS total_mrr,
        COUNT(DISTINCT s.user_id) AS unique_users
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} be
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
        ON s.subscription_id = be.subscription_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
    WHERE s.started_at <= be.event_month
        AND (s.ended_at IS NULL OR s.ended_at > be.event_month)
    GROUP BY
        DATE_TRUNC('month', be.event_month),
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)'),
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)')
)
SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    active_subscriptions,
    total_mrr,
    unique_users
FROM source
